nl_question: Return the number of likes that the high schooler named Kyle has.
sql_target: SELECT count(*) FROM Likes AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.name  =  "Kyle"

nl_question: How many high schoolers are there in grade 9 or 10?
sql_target: SELECT count(*) FROM Highschooler WHERE grade  =  9 OR grade  =  10

nl_question: What are the average and maximum number of tickets bought in all visits?
sql_target: SELECT avg(num_of_ticket) ,  max(num_of_ticket) FROM visit

nl_question: Find the name of tourney that has more than 10 matches.
sql_target: SELECT tourney_name FROM matches GROUP BY tourney_name HAVING count(*)  >  10

nl_question: Show the names of conductors and the orchestras they have conducted.
sql_target: SELECT T1.Name ,  T2.Orchestra FROM conductor AS T1 JOIN orchestra AS T2 ON T1.Conductor_ID  =  T2.Conductor_ID

nl_question: Find the model of the car whose weight is below the average weight.
sql_target: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)

nl_question: What are the country code and first name of the players who won in both tourney WTA Championships and Australian Open?
sql_target: SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN matches AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.winner_id WHERE T2.tourney_name  =  'WTA Championships' INTERSECT SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN matches AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.winner_id WHERE T2.tourney_name  =  'Australian Open'

nl_question: Find the number of visitors who did not visit any museum opened after 2010.
sql_target: SELECT count(*) FROM visitor WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT t2.visitor_id FROM museum AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID WHERE t1.open_year  >  2010)

nl_question: What are airlines that have some flight departing from airport 'AHD'?
sql_target: SELECT T1.Airline FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.Airline WHERE T2.SourceAirport  =  "AHD"

nl_question: What is the average, minimum, and maximum age for all French singers?
sql_target: SELECT avg(age) ,  min(age) ,  max(age) FROM singer WHERE country  =  'France'

nl_question: Show names of teachers and the courses they are arranged to teach in ascending alphabetical order of the teacher's name.
sql_target: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Course FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.Course_ID  =  T2.Course_ID JOIN teacher AS T3 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T3.Teacher_ID ORDER BY T3.Name

nl_question: What is the name of the course with the most students enrolled?
sql_target: SELECT  T1.course_name FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment_Courses AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T1.course_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

nl_question: List all document ids with at least two paragraphs.
sql_target: SELECT document_id FROM Paragraphs GROUP BY document_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

nl_question: What are the names of the teachers ordered by ascending age?
sql_target: SELECT Name FROM teacher ORDER BY Age ASC

nl_question: What are the Asian countries which have a population larger than that of any country in Africa?
sql_target: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia"  AND population  >  (SELECT min(population) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Africa")

nl_question: What is the code of the country with the most players?
sql_target: SELECT country_code FROM players GROUP BY country_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

nl_question: What is the first name and gender of the all the students who have more than one pet?
sql_target: SELECT T1.fname ,  T1.sex FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid GROUP BY T1.stuid HAVING count(*)  >  1

nl_question: What are the names of nations where both English and French are official languages?
sql_target: SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "French" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"

nl_question: How many type of governments are in Africa?
sql_target: SELECT count(DISTINCT GovernmentForm) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Africa"

nl_question: List the name of the conductor with the most years of work.
sql_target: SELECT Name FROM conductor ORDER BY Year_of_Work DESC LIMIT 1

nl_question: How many professionals did not operate any treatment on dogs?
sql_target: SELECT count(*) FROM Professionals WHERE professional_id NOT IN ( SELECT professional_id FROM Treatments )

nl_question: List the names and birth dates of people in ascending alphabetical order of name.
sql_target: SELECT Name ,  Birth_Date FROM people ORDER BY Name ASC

nl_question: Compute the average age of all the dogs.
sql_target: SELECT avg(age) FROM Dogs

nl_question: What is the mobile phone number of the student named Timmothy Ward ?
sql_target: select cell_mobile_number from students where first_name  =  'timmothy' and last_name  =  'ward'
